### side-panel-plugin-update.e2e.ts:470
Current code:
```ts
// Wait for everything to settle
await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3_000));

// Update dot should still be visible (plugin is still outdated)
await expect(updateDot).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });
```
The sleep is redundant — the `toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 })` assertion on the next line already polls for up to 10 seconds. Remove the sleep:
```ts
// Update dot should still be visible after rapid reloads (plugin is still outdated)
await expect(updateDot).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });
```
Increase the assertion timeout slightly to compensate for removing the sleep.

### side-panel-plugin-update.e2e.ts:556
Same pattern:
```ts
// Wait for everything to settle
await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3_000));

// Update dot should be gone (plugin is now at latest version)
await expect(updateDot).not.toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });
```
Remove the sleep and increase the assertion timeout:
```ts
// Update dot should be gone (plugin is now at latest version)
await expect(updateDot).not.toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });
```

### side-panel-reload.e2e.ts:224
Current code:
```ts
await waitForLog(server, 'Config reload complete', 15_000);
await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2_000));

// Verify the plugin card is still visible after rapid reloads.
await expect(sidePanelPage.locator('text=E2E Test')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 30_000 });
```
The `waitForLog` already waits for the server-side reload. The 2-second sleep is for the side panel UI to update. But the `toBeVisible({ timeout: 30_000 })` assertion already polls for up to 30 seconds. Remove the sleep:
```ts
await waitForLog(server, 'Config reload complete', 15_000);

// Verify the plugin card is still visible after rapid reloads.
await expect(sidePanelPage.locator('text=E2E Test')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 30_000 });
```

Constraints:
- Do NOT change any test logic or assertions beyond removing sleeps and adjusting timeouts
- Playwright's auto-retrying assertions (toBeVisible, toHaveCount) already poll — trust them
- Keep existing waitForLog calls that serve a purpose (waiting for server-side events)

Files:
